<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 07 at 4:30PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Banks,
eastern Jackson and northwestern Madison Counties through 500 PM
EDT...
At 429 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Peach State Speedway,
or near Jefferson, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Jefferson, Commerce, Homer, Maysville, Arcade, Nicholson, Ila,
Pocataligo, Peach State Speedway, Apple Valley, Neese and Banks
Crossing.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
